Antonov, Kinepolis, Omega Pharma: Benelux Equity Market Preview

-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 
2011-04-15T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/antonov-kinepolis-omega-pharma-benelux-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Benelux markets. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are from the previous close.  The  AEX-Index (AEX)  in Amsterdam declined 3.28, or 0.9 percent,
to 359.48.  Belgium ’s Bel20 Index fell 24.18, or 0.9 percent, to
2,695. Luxembourg’s LuxX Index lost 0.6 percent to 1,429.30.  Dutch stocks:  Antonov Plc (ATVAM)  : The developer of a six-speed
automatic vehicle transmission said Interim Chief Financial
Officer Mory Motabar resigned. Jackie David, finance director at
Antonov’s main operating unit, will take over his operational
responsibilities. Antonov was unchanged at 12 cents.  Belgian stocks:  Kinepolis Group NV (KIN)  : Kinohold Bis SA, which groups
most of the Bert family’s holding in Belgium’s biggest movie-
theater operator, bought an additional 39,897 Kinepolis shares
for an average 55.50 euros apiece, according to a regulatory
filing. Kinepolis advanced 0.5 percent to 55.38 euros.  Omega Pharma (OME)  NV: Belgium’s biggest supplier of
pharmacy products said first-quarter sales rose 7.8 percent to
217.8 million euros ($315.6 million), missing the 218.8 million-
euro average estimate of three analysts surveyed by Bloomberg
News. Revenue growth excluding acquisitions slowed to 3.5
percent. Omega Pharma dropped 1.3 percent to 34.67 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Martens in Brussels at 
